subject: Support setting IPMI and SSH port via redfish
commitMessage:
Support setting IPMI and SSH port via redfish

This patch adds support for configuring port of IPMI and SSH service
in redfish API. It is implemented by adding a new setPortNumber API
in service_utils which modifies the Port property in service-config-
manager.

Tested:
* PATCH with Port property works as expected.
* PATCH Port on nonexistent protocol gives PropertyUnknown error.
* Existing connections were terminated in about 15s after setting new
  port number.
* Setting port when service disabled, then enable the service, it will
  run on the new port.

Change-Id: Ibb51f7eecb863f441a1961dea957f07b9520c9c0
Signed-off-by: Jiaqing Zhao <jiaqing.zhao@intel.com>

For the "port number is null when service disabled" issue, it can be solved by calling service-config-manager to get the service info instead of calling systemd

Pros:
* Can get port number when service disabled
* Setting service enable/port will reflect immediately on redfish

Cons:
* It represents the configured status, not real status. e.g. Disabling service via systemctl will not 
make redfish to show ServiceEnabled==false unless service-config-manager restarts.
This error called out by name in COMMON_ERRORS.md.  Please read and understand that document.
This is copied from existing code, I submitted another patch (https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/50164) to fix it in current code. This patch will be rebased on it.
